╔════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║   Secure MCP Gateway — Baseline Attacks            ║
║   6 attacks against unprotected MCP2 (no S)       ║
╚════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Attack 1: Impersonation
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Sending request with fabricated caller_id and invalid signature.
Result: 200 {
  "result": {
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "API_TOKEN=sk-demo-7f3a9c2e"
      }
    ],
    "structuredContent": {
      "content": "API_TOKEN=sk-demo-7f3a9c2e"
    }
  },
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": "imp-1"
}
Expected: 200 — auth block ignored, secret returned.

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Attack 2: Replay
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Sending the exact same request twice without modification.
First : 200 [object Object]
Replay: 200 [object Object]
Expected: both succeed — no nonce deduplication.

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Attack 3: Tampering
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Sending harmless read request through MITM proxy (MITM_TAMPER=true required).
  The proxy silently rewrites the file path to point at the secret.
Result: 200 {
  "result": {
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "API_TOKEN=sk-demo-7f3a9c2e"
      }
    ],
    "structuredContent": {
      "content": "API_TOKEN=sk-demo-7f3a9c2e"
    }
  },
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": "tamper-1"
}
Expected: response contains the secret file, not the harmless file.

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Attack 4: No Session Enforcement
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Calling list_allowed_directories with no s.init/s.ready handshake.
Result: 200 [object Object]
Expected: 200 — no session state machine enforced.

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Attack 5: Unauthorized Tool Access
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Calling read_file on the secret path — no ACL enforcement in baseline.
Result: 200 {
  "result": {
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "API_TOKEN=sk-demo-7f3a9c2e"
      }
    ],
    "structuredContent": {
      "content": "API_TOKEN=sk-demo-7f3a9c2e"
    }
  },
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": "acl-1"
}
Expected: 200 — secret content returned, no capability check.

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Attack 6: MITM Visibility
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Routing request through MITM proxy without tampering.
  Check proxy console output — full plaintext request and response are logged.
Result: 200 [object Object]
Expected: 200 — proxy intercepted and logged the full exchange.
